<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HBO Pictures is adding three new productions to its roster of 1989 films. 
Albert Finney will play a TV news personality facing a personal crisis in "The 
Image," scheduled to start shooting in May. Pierce Brosnan, Tom Skerritt and 
Wendy Hughes star in "Heist," a race track robbery suspense film under way in 
San Diego and Del Mar. And beginning next week in Toronto will be "Perfect 
Witness," a court system drama with Brian Dennehy, Aidan Quinn and Stockard 
Channing. Recently completed in Atlanta and New Orleans was "Traveling Man," 
with John Lithgow, which will debut June 25 on HBO. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
