<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 9A; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
310 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Barry hit a home run in the sixth inning to help San Diego State defeat 
host New Orleans, 4-3. Lance Pinnell had two RBIs for the Aztecs (25-14). 
Plantenberg (4-3) was the winning pitcher. New Orleans is 15-19. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Kevin Tahan hit his school-record-tying 12th homer of the year in the 
first inning, and collected three other hits in U.S. International University's 
come-from-behind 7-6 victory over visiting Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Tahan, a senior from Patrick Henry, was 4 for 5 with two RBI, including two 
doubles. 
</P>
<P>
USIU improved to 14-26; 25th-ranked Fullerton dropped to 23-14. 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene College lost to visiting Westmont College, 7-4 and 7-3, in 
a Golden State Athletic Conference doubleheader. Point Loma Nazarene dropped to 
17-20, 5-10. Westmont improved to 21-13, 10-5. 
</P>
<P>
After host USD scored two runs in the top of the ninth inning for a two-run 
lead over Claremont-Mudd, the visitors rallied with three run for a 6-5 victory 
at Cunningham Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
USD needed only singles matches to defeat visiting UC Irvine, 6-0. Jennifer 
Larking defeated Courtney Weichsel, 6-0, 6-0, at No. 1. The Toreras improved to 
17-6. 
</P>
<P>
The 15th-ranked San Diego State women's team defeated host USIU, 5-1, in a 
nonconference match. Sondra Mitchell defeated USIU's Diane Lowings, 6-4, 6-3, 
at No 1 singles. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S GOLF 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International's John Adams shot a one-under 71 as the Gulls won the Grand 
Canyon Invitational tournament in Phoenix by 14 strokes over Washington State. 
USIU was first with 856 points, USD was seventh (898) and Point Loma Nazarene 
College was 12th (950). 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
USD (19-20) swept a nonconference doubleheader from host La Verne, 2-1 and 5-1, 
behind the pitching of Lisa Ziomkowski and Jeanne Weinsheim. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Babcock had 15 kills and 17 digs to help UCSD defeat visiting La Verne, 
15-4, 15-5, 15-9. 
</P>
