</P>
<P>
Aug. 29: Goode Beethoven at the Bowl (Richard Goode, piano). 
</P>
<P>
Aug. 30: Vocal Delights: A Celebration of British and American Songs (Cleo 
Laine). 
</P>
<P>
Aug. 31: DeWaart Conducts Beethoven. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 1-2: Symphonic Sass: Sarah Vaughan and Ramsey Lewis with the L.A. 
Philharmonic. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 5: Previn Conducts Beethoven's Fifth. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 6: All That Jazz (Dizzy Gillespie). 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 7: Stars and Strauss Forever. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 8-9: John Williams: The Music of Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 12: Favorites for a Summer Evening. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 13: A Bowl Full of Blues (B. B. King, Joe Williams and Etta James). 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 14: Pathetique by Tchaikovsky; Violin Magic by Mendelssohn. 
</P>
<P>
Sept. 15-16: Fireworks Finale. 
</P>
