<P>
Voters in Deadwood, S.D., the Black Hills town where Wild Bill Hickok was shot 
to death in a card game, approved a return to legalized gambling. City leaders 
hope games of chance will revive the economy and plan to use proceeds to 
restore historic buildings and public facilities. The measure to legalize 
poker, blackjack and slot machines received 690 votes to 230 votes against. 
Hickok, a U.S. marshal and frontiersman, was shot in the back of the head in 
1876 during a poker game in a saloon called No. 10. Legend has it he was 
holding a pair each of aces and eights, known since as the "dead man's hand." 
