<P>
NEW TOSHIBA CHIP TO HAVE FAST ACCESS TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Toshiba Corp., the Japanese electronics company, said it will soon market a new 
memory chip with the world's fastest access time. 
</P>
<P>
Toshiba said the new product has a maximum access time of 20 nanoseconds or 20 
billionths of a second. The company also plans to introduce 25 and 35 
nanosecond versions. 
</P>
<P>
Sample prices of 20, 25 and 35 nanosecond versions range from $60.4 to $113.2, 
the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Sample shipments will start in May and mass production will begin in the summer 
at a monthly rate of 30,000 units. 
</P>
