<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
2 MEN GUNNED DOWN IN SEPARATE EARLY-MORNING SANTA ANA SHOOTINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Santa Ana men were killed early this morning about an hour apart in 
separate incidents. 
</P>
<P>
Police received reports of gunfire in the 1500 block of South Standard Avenue 
about 1:30 a.m., Santa Ana Police Lt. Bob Chavez said. When officers arrived, 
they found the body of Esequiel Martinez, 32, of Santa Ana lying in an alley. 
He had been shot once, Chavez said. Police have no suspects. 
</P>
<P>
In the second incident, Aaron Olivos, 32, was shot about 2:30 a.m. in the 1900 
block of West 1st Street. 
</P>
<P>
Chavez said Olivos was driving east on 1st Street approaching Daisy Avenue when 
he was cut off by another driver who had pulled out of a driveway. 
</P>
<P>
"Olivos honked, got out of his car and approached the other car. He was 
immediately shot one time from the passenger's side of the vehicle," Chavez 
said. Olivos suffered a single gunshot wound to the right side from a small 
caliber handgun and died at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses saw a red compact car drive east on 1st Street after the shooting, 
but they could not describe the passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
