<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION; 
</P>
<P>
CAPTAIN MAY GET DRUNK FOR DEFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fired captain of the Exxon Valdez oil tanker, source of the worst oil spill 
in North American history, may fight allegations that he was intoxicated at the 
time of the accident by getting drunk under a doctor's supervision, his lawyer 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Capt. Joseph Hazelwood, who failed an alcohol test 10 hours after the ship's 
grounding, may get drunk this week in Portland, Ore., to see how fast his body 
assimilates liquor, Seattle lawyer Michael Williamson said. "We're trying to 
find out the rate at which his body burns off alcohol -- everyone's body burns 
off alcohol at a different rate," Williamson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
