<HEADLINE>
<P>
MCENROE OUTCLASSES BORG 6-3, 6-3 IN SINGAPORE MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SINGAPORE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John McEnroe outclassed a rusty Bjorn Borg of Sweden 6-3, 6-3 in an exhibition 
tennis match today. 
</P>
<P>
A genial McEnroe totally dominated the indoor contest played at the 
air-conditioned World Trade Center. The 30-year-old American currently is 
ranked sixth in world standings. 
</P>
<P>
Singapore was the first stop this week for Borg and McEnroe on what is touted 
as their "reunion tour" that includes the Philippines, Taiwan and Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Borg, 32, told reporters that the Asian tour was his farewell. "There will be 
no more tennis for me," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
